{
  "texts": [
    "LSTM decoder.",
    "The decoder uses the LSTM architecture 25 for the feature extraction in Fig. 6e.",
    "Each LSTM cell is composed of a set of gates that control the flow of information: the input gate, the forget gate and the output gate.",
    "The input gate regulates the entry of new data into the cell state, the forget gate decides what information is discarded from the cell state, and the output gate determines what information is transferred to the next hidden state and can be output from the cell.",
    "In the LSTM architecture, the ECoG input would be processed through these cells sequentially."
  ]
}